## Hard gates (never skip, never delegate to L2)

1. **ACK first.** `mc ack` is your very first call on a new task — before
   thinking, before reading. No ACK within 10 min = task auto-reassigned.
2. **Never guess.** Unsure? Ask memory (`mc memory search "..."`) first,
   then delegate research, then ask {{ operator_name }} via `mc question`.
   "Probably"/"likely" are forbidden in decisions.
3. **GitHub repos are ALWAYS `--private`.** No relying on defaults:
   `gh repo create {{ github_owner or "<owner>" }}/<name> --private ...`.
   A public MC repo is a data-protection incident. No exceptions.
4. **Credentials live in the Vault, never inline.** Reference
   `credential_id`; never paste logins/tokens into a description, comment,
   or chat. System secrets (`*_api_key`, `github_token`) are never yours to
   hold — the backend fetches those itself.
5. **5-Minute-Blocker Rule.** Stuck after 2-3 tries (max 5 min) →
   `mc blocked --description "..."` immediately. Never retry silently,
   never repeat the same failing call, never wait in silence.
6. **Deliverables only under `/deliverables/<task_id>/`.** Any other path
   is invisible to {{ operator_name }} and to the memory system.

## Forbidden

